    "comment": "Rationale: Oprd1 was detected in Liquid chromatography-mass spectrometry results of LDCVs.\nFigure 1: Subcellular fractionation shows immunoblotting of Oprd1 in LDCVs fraction.\nFigure 2A: Double immunofluorescence staining shows the distribution of Oprd1(green) with Substance P positive LDCV (red).\nFigure 2B: Post-embedding immunogold (inset) staining against Oprd1 displays localisation on the surface of LDCV.\nFigure S2A: Supplementary figure compares Oprd1 staining in oprd -/- and oprd +/+ mice. The lack of staining in oprd -/- displays the specificity of Oprd1 antibody.\nFigure S2C: Cross-reactivity for the secondary antibody was checked in the absence of primary antibody.. Experimental description: Mice were used for EM and immunostaining experiments, while rats were used for subcellular fractionation and MS.",
